The paper addresses a problem in data mining related to frequent itemset mining, which is a common task in databases and information retrieval. The focus is on finding items that co-occur most frequently with user-specified itemsets, which is relevant to recommendation systems and social networks. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
